# Seismo 0.6 Architecture

## Layer boundaries (keep them hard)

| Layer | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| **Controllers** | Orchestrate request/response only |
| **Services / fetchers** | Business logic, external I/O |
| **Repositories** | All SQL and persistence |
| **Views** | Render only — no business logic |

## SQL placement

- **No SQL** outside `src/Repository/`, except numbered migrations in `src/Migration/`.
- **Schema changes:** add the next numbered migration and update `docs/db-schema.sql` to match.

## URLs and paths

- Never hardcode app URLs or path prefixes for internal links/redirects.
- Always use `getBasePath()` (see `bootstrap.php`).

## Satellite-aware reads

- Use `entryTable()` **only** for entry-source tables (`feed_items`, `lex_items`, `calendar_events`, `feeds`, `emails`, etc.).
- Keep local-only tables bare: `entry_scores`, `system_config`, `magnitu_*`, `entry_favourites`, cron mutex state.

## Refresh pipeline

- Cron CLI and web “refresh” actions must call the **same** underlying service implementation—no duplicate ingest logic.
- Respect `CronMutexRepository` / refresh mutex so overlapping cron and browser refresh cannot corrupt chunked cursors.

## Admin UI ownership

- Feeds, Scraper, and Mail configuration live on **their module pages**—do not add one-off settings elsewhere.
